defs.name: best_containing
defs.value:
pub fn best_containing(&Self, Block::Hash, Option<NumberFor<Block>>,
                       &RwLock<()>) -> Result<Option<Block::Hash>>
defs.docs:
Get the most recent block hash of the best (longest) chains
 that contain block with the given `target_hash`.

attributes.value: / Get the most recent block hash of the best (longest) chains
/ that contain block with the given `target_hash`.
/ The search space is always limited to blocks which are in the finalized
/ chain or descendents of it.
/ If `maybe_max_block_number` is `Some(max_block_number)`
/ the search is limited to block `numbers <= max_block_number`.
/ in other words as if there were no blocks greater `max_block_number`.
/ Returns `Ok(None)` if `target_hash` is not found in search space.
/ TODO: document time complexity of this, see [#1444](https://github.com/paritytech/substrate/issues/1444)

defs.name: lowest_common_ancestor
defs.value:
pub fn lowest_common_ancestor<Block: BlockT, T: HeaderMetadata<Block> +
                              ?Sized>(&T, Block::Hash, Block::Hash)
-> Result<HashAndNumber<Block>, T::Error>
defs.docs: Get lowest common ancestor between two blocks in the tree.

attributes.value: / Get lowest common ancestor between two blocks in the tree.
/ This implementation is efficient because our trees have very few and
/ small branches, and because of our current query pattern:
/ lca(best, final), lca(best + 1, final), lca(best + 2, final), etc.
/ The first call is O(h) but the others are O(1).

defs.name: TreeRoute
defs.docs: A tree-route from one block to another in the chain.

attributes.value: / A tree-route from one block to another in the chain.
/ All blocks prior to the pivot in the deque is the reverse-order unique ancestry
/ of the first block, the block at the pivot index is the common ancestor,
/ and all blocks after the pivot is the ancestry of the second block, in
/ order.
/ The ancestry sets will include the given blocks, and thus the tree-route is
/ never empty.
/ ```text
/ Tree route from R1 to E2. Retracted is [R1, R2, R3], Common is C, enacted [E1, E2]
/ C
/ ```text
/ Tree route from C to E2. Retracted empty. Common is C, enacted [E1, E2]

defs.name: Error
defs.value:
pub enum Error {
    OneShotCancelled(futures::channel::oneshot::Canceled),
    Consensus(sp_consensus::Error),
    Backend(String),
    UnknownBlock(String),
    ApplyExtrinsicFailed(ApplyExtrinsicFailed),
    InvalidChildType,
    ExtrinsicRootInvalid {
        received: String,
        expected: String,
    },
    Execution(Box<dyn sp_state_machine::Error>),
    Blockchain(Box<Error>),
    StorageChanges(sp_state_machine::DefaultError),
    InvalidChildStorageKey,
    InvalidAuthoritiesSet,
    VersionInvalid(String),
    GenesisInvalid,
    JustificationDecode,
    BadJustification(String),
    NotAvailableOnLightClient,
    InvalidCHTProof,
    RemoteFetchCancelled,
    RemoteFetchFailed,
    CallResultDecode(&'static str, CodecError),
    RuntimeApiError(ApiError),
    RuntimeCodeMissing,
    ChangesTriesNotSupported,
    ErrorReadingChangesTriesConfig,
    ChangesTrieAccessFailed(String),
    NonSequentialFinalization(String),
    NotInFinalizedChain,
    MissingHashRequiredForCHT,
    InvalidStateRoot,
    IncompletePipeline,
    TransactionPoolNotReady,
    DatabaseError(sp_database::error::DatabaseError),
    MissingHeader(String),
    StateDatabase(String),
    Application(Box<dyn std::error::Error + Send + Sync + 'static>),
    RuntimeCode(&'static str),
    Storage(String),
}
